The paper deals with a geometric range space and the problem of finding a subset that maximizes a given function. This suggests that the paper belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The function being optimized is related to statistical discrepancy, which is a measure of how well a set of points is distributed in a space. This connects the paper to the sub-categories of data mining (cs.DM), machine learning (cs.LG), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
